CodesCompiler is a beginner-friendly online platform designed to help people learn web development in a simple, practical way. It focuses mainly on the core building blocks of the web—HTML, CSS, and JavaScript—and allows users to practice coding directly in their browser. CodesCompiler is built around the idea of learning by doing. Instead of just reading theory, users can write and run real code instantly without installing any software. The platform is completely free and does not require sign-up, making it very accessible for beginners.